  "story": {
    "title": "The Truth in the Forest",
    "body": "One morning, Nila decided to wake up early and go for a walk. She did not want to stay home anymore. She walked toward the deep forest near her village. As she entered, she heard a strange sound from the ground. She looked carefully and saw a small creature sleeping under a berry bush. Nila had a serious decision to make — should she disturb it or leave? She chose to collect some berries quietly and prepare to leave. Suddenly, the creature woke up. Nila froze. But the creature only looked at her and began a gentle conversation with its eyes. Nila smiled. She wanted to introduce it to her friends, but she knew that was not possible. Either way, she felt happy. As she sailed back home through the river path, she thought about the truth she had learned — that nature holds secrets for those who spend time in silence. She never forgot that morning.",
    "comprehension": [
